speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for War (1) whether it is intended to mechanise any part of the Cavalry Militia Force;

(2) when the last inspection of existing units of the Cavalry Militia Force took place by the Inspector-General of Cavalry; when it is intended to hold the next inspection; and whether any of the officers of such units will be afforded the opportunity of attending a course at the Cavalry School, Weedon;

(3) the duties of the clergyman appearing in the Army List as honorary chaplain to the North Irish Horse, Cavalry Militia; how many church parades have been held during the past two years for officers and other ranks; and whether the attendance has been voluntary or compulsory?
